If you want historically accurate stories and costumes watch Isabel And Ministerio del tiempo. Or really any period drama from Spain. But y’all scared of a subtitle so have fun staying mad

Anyway my point is that the costume choices in period dramas aren’t made to be accurate they’re made to say something creatively about the story we’re watching, not so some sour bitch on the internet can stay mad about it 😂

“Hmmm why are they wearing corsets under empire waist gowns?” They’re looking at pretty dresses that look vaguely old fashioned in a world where dukes and viscounts are all sexy and wear riding boots with every outfit

Bridgerton, the featheringtons in particular are meant to be tacky. Do you know how much all that COLORED fabric would have cost back in the day??? And it is again a show that’s meant to be decadent and indulgent and a regular audience member isn’t going to watch this and think

Take reign for example. Literally the most historically inaccurate show ever made and that’s the POINT. It’s meant to feel like gossip girl. The costumes are prom dresses from Macy’s because it’s meant to be accessible to the audience. These are the it girls of ye olden times
